						               													<description>Fed up with the foolishness of mortals, the Gods of Olympus have gathered to debate the fate of mankind...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An exciting, strategic 2 player game puts the power of the 12 Olympian Gods in your hands!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;NOW AVAILABLE ON TABLE TOP SIMULATOR: https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=2629187044&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Take control of the 12 Olympian Gods and Goddesses and use the powers of Zeus, Hera, Apollo, Poseidon, Hermes, Artemis, Athena, Dionysus, Ares, Aphrodite, Hephaestus, and Hades. Each brings a unique ability that can alter the fate of your competition.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Who will be the first to cross Mount Olympus?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player is provided 12 Gods of Olympus cards, light and dark.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The gods and goddesses have individualized health points, movements, attacks and special abilities that match their characteristics, to deeply tie theme in with mechanics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is played on a 9x9 diagonal board. The first space on both sides are the &amp;quot;gates&amp;quot; spaces. It will be your goal to either eliminate all the other player's characters, or move any of your characters onto your opponent's gate space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your first turn, select a character to &amp;quot;summon&amp;quot; onto your gates space. On subsequent turns, you will choose to move, attack, or bring additional characters into play.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All of the cards are balanced so that they are equal in power. Zeus has twice as much health as Hermes, Hermes has far more mobility and provides a &amp;quot;Winged Sandals&amp;quot; ability that increases the movement of other pieces. Athena has even less health, but a powerful &amp;quot;Aegis Shield&amp;quot; ability protects other pieces. All characters will be equally important to achieving your victory.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Expansions will add deck building and asymmetric gameplay options.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Try playing chess with each of the 12 Greek Gods as your pieces.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
